---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout title="CPPoliTO">
	<main>
		<h1><span class="text-gradient">CPPoliTO</span></h1>

		<p class="instructions">
			Welcome to the official website of the student team 
			<strong>Competitive Programming Politecnico di Torino</strong>!
			<br />

			We are a group of competitive programmers actively engaged in national and international coding competitions,
			proudly representing <a herf="https://www.polito.it/">PoliTO</a>.
			<br />
			Famous for our expertise in coding, algorithms, and complex data structures,
			we tackle challenges with our skills.
			<br />
			Beyond competitions, many of us excel as software engineers in top tech companies.
			<br />
			With a knack for mathematics and a passion for problem-solving,
			we redefine what it means to be super cool programmers!
			<br />

			If you have any suggestions related to the web page, please reach us on
			<a href="https://github.com/CPPoliTO/cppolito">GitHub</a>.
		</p>
		<p class="bulletBody">
			Why consider Competitive Programming?
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Professional growth: </strong>
					It's like a superpower for acing job interviews at big tech companies.
					It's the best way to prepare for landing great Software Engineering jobs.
					Plus, all major tech companies use it in their technical interviews.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Problem soliving: </strong>
					It's fun and helps you become better at solving problems and coding like a pro.
					Think of it as a cool programmers club where you learn and grow together.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Team work: </strong>
					We thrive in teams of three, combining diverse algorithms and mindsets
					to tackle challenges effectively, especially in competitions.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Valuable networking: </strong>
					You'll meet lots of cool people and companies at events
					like <a herf="https://swerc.eu/2023">SWERC</a>
					who really want to hire people like you.
					They love how good you get at solving tough problems!
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Sponsored student trips: </strong>
					Exciting opportunities await, including fully funded trips to amazing

					<a herf="https://swerc.eu/2023">SWERC</a> locations.
					Recent venues have included Milan, Paris, and Porto,
					offering unforgettable experiences alongside invaluable learning opportunities.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</p>

		<p class="instructions">
			Celebrating Our Success at SWERC 2024:
			<br />

			We're thrilled to announce our stellar performance in this year's SWERC 2024 competition!
			Our team, OverkillaTO, achieved an impressive 21st rank out of over 110 competing teams,
			making it our best result since the team's inception. As the 5th-ranked Italian university team,
			we're incredibly proud of our accomplishments.
			<br />

			Team OverkillaTO comprises Nima Naderi Ghotbodini, Federico Fortunati, and Mattia Longo,
			whose dedication and expertise propelled us to this remarkable achievement.
			Additionally, another one of our teams represented by Pasquale Bianco, Lorenzo Nikiforos, and Antonio Spadaro 
			secured the 85th rank, further highlighting our collective prowess.
			<br />

			With each competition, we strive for even better results,
			pushing the boundaries of excellence in competitive programming.
			Join us as we continue to raise the bar and set new milestones in the world of coding!
			<br />

			Read more: <a href="https://www.polito.it/ateneo/comunicazione-e-ufficio-stampa/poliflash/sfidarsi-nella-programmazione-informatica-i-successi-del">
			University's offical post
			</a>, 
			<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/politecnico-di-torino_polito-awards-poliflash-activity-7168236949000839169-q9L3?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop">
			University's LinkedIn post
			</a>, 
			<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7158514095971803137">
			Our LinkedIn post
			</a>
		</p>
		
		<ul role="list" class="link-card-grid">
			<Card
				href="https://codeforces.com/group/w6aXjpwI9u/blog/entry/11405"
				title="SWERC 2023/24 Selection"
				body="The selections for ICPC/SWERC 2023/24 are open! More details here."
			/>
			<Card
				href="https://linktr.ee/cppolito"
				title="Linktree"
				body="Follow us on social media and join our groups to stay updated on our activities!"
			/>
		</ul>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		max-width: 60ch;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.text-gradient {
		background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-size: 400%;
		background-position: 0%;
	}
	.instructions {
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent), 25%);
		background-color: white;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 0.4rem;
	}
	.instructions code {
		font-size: 0.875em;
		font-weight: bold;
		background: rgba(var(--accent), 12%);
		color: rgb(var(--accent));
		border-radius: 4px;
		padding: 0.3em 0.45em;
	}
	.instructions strong {
		color: rgb(var(--accent));
	}
	.link-card-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(24ch, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 0;
	}
	ul, bulletBody {
		list-style-type: none; /* Remove default bullet points */
		margin-top: 1rem;
		padding-left: 2rem;
		background-color: #006400; /* Dark green background color */
		color: #fff; /* Text color */
	}

	ul li {
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 1.5rem; /* Adjust padding for text */
	}

	ul li:before {
		content: '\2022'; /* Unicode for a bullet (you can change this to any character you like) */
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: #f0f; /* Color of bullet */
	}
</style>
